{{ infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = Henry C. Bradsby | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- uncomment the template to use it: {{Birth date and age|year|mo|da}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Historian and biographer | language = English | nationality = | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = United States local history | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | portaldisp = }}
'''Colonel Henry C. Bradsby,''' often credited as '''H.C. Bradsby,''' was a late 19th-century historian and biographer. Many of his works are extensive local histories of various United States counties in [[Illinois]], [[Missouri]], [[Indiana]] and [[Pennsylvania]], several more than a thousand pages long at their original publication.
==Works== * ''History of Arkansas'' * ''Battle of Gettysburg'' * ''History of Illinois'' * ''History of Bureau County, Illinois'' (1885) * ''History of Cumberland and Adams Counties, Pennsylvania'' (1886) with Aaron Sheely, M.A. Leeson, and others * ''History of Columbia and Montour Counties, Pennsylvania'' (1887) with Samuel P. Bates, H.C. Bell, J.H. Battle * ''Commemorative biographical and historical record of Kane County, Illinois'' (1888) * ''History of Vigo County, Indiana, with Biographical Selections'' (1891) * ''History of Bradford county, Pennsylvania, with biographical selections'' (1891) * ''History of Luzerne County Pennsylvania'' (1893)
