{{multiple issues| {{more footnotes|date=January 2013}} {{Notability|Academics|date=September 2010}} }}
'''Tom Behan''' (22 June 1957 – 30 August 2010) was an academic and writer on Italian history, politics and culture and an active member of the British [[Socialist Workers Party (Britain)|Socialist Workers Party]] for over 30 years.<ref>http://www.socialistworker.co.uk/art.php?id=22302</ref> He was a Senior Lecturer in Italian at the [[University of Kent]] at Canterbury,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kent.ac.uk/secl/italian/staff/t-behan.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609185036/http://www.kent.ac.uk/secl/italian/staff/t-behan.html |archivedate=2011-06-09 |df= }}</ref> author of the first political biography of Europe's leading radical playwright and winner of the 1997 Nobel Prize for Literature [[Dario Fo]],<ref>http://us.macmillan.com/author/tombehan</ref> and an authority on Italian organised crime.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fhm.com/upgrade/work/working-for-the-mafia-20090204 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-09-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725084530/http://www.fhm.com/upgrade/work/working-for-the-mafia-20090204 |archivedate=2011-07-25 |df= }}</ref>
==Selected bibliography== *''Forward to 1921 : the dissolution of the Italian Communist Party'' (1991) *''The Camorra'' (1996) *[http://pubs.socialistreviewindex.org.uk/sr214/behan.htm ''Workers' Playtime: Dario Fo''] (1997) *''The long awaited moment : the working class and the Italian Communist Party in Milan, 1943-1948'' (1997) *[http://pubs.socialistreviewindex.org.uk/isj84/behan.htm ''Interview: the return of Italian Communism?''] (1999) *''Dario Fo: Revolutionary Theatre'' (2000) *[http://pubs.socialistreviewindex.org.uk/isj92/behan.htm ''Genoa: Nothing can be the same again''] (2001) *''See Naples and die : the Camorra and organised crime'' (2002) *''The resistible rise of Benito Mussolini'' (2003) *[http://www.socialistworker.co.uk/art.php?id=12598 ''The legacy of Giuseppe Garibaldi - the 19th century's Che Guevara''] (2007) *[http://www.socialistworker.co.uk/art.php?id=12692 ''Giovanni Pesce: leading Italian partisan, who kept fighting for freedom''] (2007) *''Defiance : the story of one man who stood up to the Sicilian mafia'' (2008) *[http://www.socialistworker.co.uk/art.php?id=13971 ''How capitalism created the mafia''] (2008) *[http://www.socialistworker.co.uk/art.php?id=15053 ''Aldo Moro killing: a miscalculation that almost destroyed the Italian left''] (2008) *''The Italian Resistance : fascists, guerrillas and the Allies'' (2009)
